# nyne Virtual Filesystem

> This project is mounted via **nyne** — a FUSE overlay at `{{ source_dir }}`.
> **Prefer the Read tool** for reading virtual files. Use Bash (`cat`, `echo >`, `sed -i`) for batch reads, writes, and pipelines. All `@`-namespaced entries are real files.

## Reading Code

```sh
# File-level overview (symbol table, metadata)
cat file.{{ ext }}@/OVERVIEW.md

# Symbols directory overview
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/OVERVIEW.md

# Read a specific symbol body
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/my_function.{{ ext }}

# Read imports
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/imports.{{ ext }}

# Read specific lines
cat file.{{ ext }}@/lines:10-20
```

**Always read `OVERVIEW.md` first** to discover exact symbol names before accessing symbols.

## Editing Code

| Task | Command |
|-|-|
| Rewrite a function | `echo 'new body' > file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/body.{{ ext }}` |
| Edit imports | Write to `file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/imports.{{ ext }}` |
| Append after a symbol | Append to `file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/body.{{ ext }}` |
| Change a signature | Write to `file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/signature.{{ ext }}` |
| Clear a docstring | Truncate `file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/docstring.txt` |

Writes are **validated by tree-sitter** and **auto-formatted** before splicing back.

## Symbol Naming

- Top-level: `symbols/my_function.{{ ext }}`
- Trait/interface impls: `symbols/Display_for_Foo.{{ ext }}`
- Collisions get `~Kind` suffix: `symbols/Foo~Struct.{{ ext }}`
- Nested methods: `symbols/Foo~Impl@/new.{{ ext }}`

## Git

```sh
cat file.{{ ext }}@/git/BLAME.md          # per-line authorship
cat file.{{ ext }}@/git/LOG.md            # commit log
cat file.{{ ext }}@/git/CONTRIBUTORS.md   # contributors
cat @/git/STATUS.md                       # repo status
```

## Repository Level

```sh
cat @/STATUS.md     # mount status
cat @/GUIDE.md      # full nyne guide
```
